ANKARA , December 15 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Iraq 's Kurdistan Democratic Party -LRB- KDP -RRB- forces killed nine militants of Turkey 's outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party -LRB- PKK -RRB- in northern Iraq , the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today .
The agency quoted a radio report from the KDP , one of the two major Kurdish groups in northern Iraq , as saying that the PKK militants had attacked a civil vehicle near Baneka village in northern Iraq and killed six Christian Kurds in the attack .
Following the attack , the report said , the KDP forces surrounded the group of PKK militants , nine of them were killed in the clash .
The report did not say when the clash occurred .
